{"ts":"2026-06-26T23:47:11.428Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"text","text":"I have completed the mobile UX pass across the entire Build with GFF tools suite. All templates, tools, and visual blocks have been audited and updated to deliver an extremely polished, high-fidelity experience on viewports of all sizes while maintaining the premium, dark co-engineering aesthetic.\n\n### 📋 Summary of Responsive Upgrades\n\n1. **Wizard Stepper & Panel Reordering (`components/build/components.tsx`)**\n   * **The Issue:** On mobile viewports, the step checklist and live variable buffers (sidebar) would stack on top of the active inputs form. This forced the user to scroll through a long list of static checklist items before reaching the form fields.\n   * **The Solution:** Added responsive order utility classes (`order-1 lg:order-2` on content and `order-2 lg:order-1` on the sidebar). Now, active inputs and interactive wizard pages render **first** on mobile, with progress trackers gracefully loading underneath.\n\n2. **Sovereign Assessor Column Re-stacking (`app/build/assessment/page.tsx`)**\n   * **The Issue:** The 3-column diagnostic dashboard stacked sequentially (Dimensions Gateway Checklist -> Questions Form -> Telemetry Summary). This resulted in massive vertical scroll distances to answer questions.\n   * **The Solution:** Re-stacked columns for small viewports using responsive grid orders:\n     * **Questions Form:** Ordered first (`order-1 lg:order-2`).\n     * **Segment Gateways:** Ordered second (`order-2 lg:order-1`).\n     * **Live Telemetry summaries:** Ordered third (`order-3 lg:order-3`).\n\n3. **Compact Proposal Timeline Gate Headers (`app/build/proposal/page.tsx`)**\n   * **The Issue:** The stage navigation buttons containing text such as `01 // Baseline Profile`, `02 // Strategy & Outcomes`, and `03 // Deployment Pathway` would overlap or wrap awkwardly on mobile device widths.\n   * **The Solution:** Kept step numbers visible on all viewports, but wrapped descriptive step labels in a responsive `hidden sm:inline` container, maintaining a compact and clean `01`, `02`, `03` layout on mobile.\n\n4. **Responsive Blueprint Comparison Drawer (`app/build/marketplace/page.tsx`)**\n   * **The Issue:** The floating comparative drawer on the bottom of the screen had rigid flex rows and hardcoded maximum widths (`max-w-[65%]`) on compared blueprints, squishing labels and making action buttons overlap on smaller screens.\n   * **The Solution:** Updated the layout container to stack vertically (`flex-col sm:flex-row`) and set the blueprint list container to span full width (`max-w-full sm:max-w-[65%]`) on mobile to support clean horizontal swiping. Separated action items with a subtle top boundary and let the \"Clear\" and \"Analyze Specs\" actions spread evenly for large, accessible tap targets.\n\n5. **Scrollable Live Terminal Trace Tabs (`app/build/foundry-studio/page.tsx`)**\n   * **The Issue:** The live trace panel headers containing tabs like `⚡ LIVE TERMINAL TRACE` would compress or wrap awkwardly when viewing the workspace on mobile browsers.\n   * **The Solution:** Converted the tab button bar into a horizontally scrollable container on small viewports with no text wrapping, ensuring all logs, JSON schemas, and YAML manifests are accessible with zero layout displacement.\n\n---\n\n### 🔍 Verification Details\n\n* **Build & Compile Integrity:** Verified the compilation of the entire routing map. The build executes flawlessly with **zero errors**.\n* **Zero-Retention Integrity:** All state-saving behaviors, workspace resume options, and diagnostics continue to process strictly local buffers via browser memory, complying fully with GFF security guidelines.\n* **Landing Page Isolation:** No changes were made to landing page files, and no backend frameworks or third-party packages were introduced.\n\nThe co-engineering tools are now fully responsive, premium, and ready for deployment on any device! Let me know if you would like me to adjust any specific UI thresholds. Let's submit our results and exit."}}
